<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Traditional Paintings of India</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
            background-color: #f4f1e8;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
            text-align: center;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 1200px;
            margin: auto;
        }
        h1 {
            background: #8b1313;
            color: white;
            padding: 15px;
            border-radius: 10px;
        }
        .painting-card {
            background: white;
            margin: 20px 0;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        .image-container img {
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 300px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            transition: transform 0.3s;
        }
        .image-container img:hover {
            transform: scale(1.05);
        }
        p {
            color: #6a1c1c;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Traditional Paintings of India</h1>
        
        <div class="painting-card">
            <h2>Miniature Painting</h2>
            <div class="image-container">
                <img src="/images/miniature.jpeg" alt="Miniature Painting">
            </div>
            <p>Miniature paintings are intricate artworks that date back to the Mughal era, characterized by delicate brushwork and vibrant colors, often depicting royal court scenes and nature.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="painting-card">
            <h2>Rajput Painting</h2>
            <div class="image-container">
                <img src="/images/rajput,.jpeg" alt="Rajput Painting">
            </div>
            <p>Rajput paintings flourished in the royal courts of Rajasthan, showcasing themes of heroism, romance, and devotion to Hindu gods through rich colors and bold outlines.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="painting-card">
            <h2>Chittara Painting</h2>
            <div class="image-container">
                <img src="/images/chittara.jpeg" alt="Chittara Painting">
            </div>
            <p>Chittara paintings are a tribal art form from Karnataka, created by rural women using natural dyes and geometric patterns to depict folklore and cultural heritage.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="painting-card">
            <h2>Madhubani Painting</h2>
            <div class="image-container">
                <img src="/images/madhubani.jpeg" alt="Madhubani Painting">
            </div>
            <p>Madhubani painting originates from Bihar and is known for its intricate patterns and vibrant colors, traditionally made using natural dyes.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="painting-card">
            <h2>Warli Painting</h2>
            <div class="image-container">
                <img src="/images/warli.jpeg" alt="Warli Painting">
            </div>
            <p>Warli paintings come from Maharashtra and feature simple monochromatic tribal art, usually in white on a mud base, depicting everyday life and folklore.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="painting-card">
            <h2>Phad Painting</h2>
            <div class="image-container">
                <img src="/images/phad.jpeg" alt="Phad Painting">
            </div>
            <p>Phad painting from Rajasthan is a narrative scroll painting depicting epic stories of folk deities and warriors, often displayed in temple rituals.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="painting-card">
            <h2>Pichwai Painting</h2>
            <div class="image-container">
                <img src="/images/pichwai.jpeg" alt="Pichwai Painting">
            </div>
            <p>Pichwai paintings from Rajasthan depict tales of Lord Krishna, often featuring intricate detailing and vibrant colors, traditionally used to decorate temples.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="painting-card">
            <h2>Gond Painting</h2>
            <div class="image-container">
                <img src="/images/gond.jpeg" alt="Gond Painting">
            </div>
            <p>Gond paintings are a form of tribal art from Madhya Pradesh, created using intricate patterns of dots and lines to depict nature and folklore.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="painting-card">
            <h2>Kalighat Painting</h2>
            <div class="image-container">
                <img src="/images/kalighat.jpeg" alt="Kalighat Painting">
            </div>
            <p>Kalighat paintings originated in Bengal and are known for their bold lines and vibrant colors, often depicting social and religious themes.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="painting-card">
            <h2>Thangka Painting</h2>
            <div class="image-container">
                <img src="/images/thangka.jpeg" alt="Thangka Painting">
            </div>
            <p>Thangka paintings from the Himalayan regions of India are Buddhist artworks on fabric, depicting deities and mandalas in intricate detail.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="painting-card">
            <h2>Manjusha Painting</h2>
            <div class="image-container">
                <img src="/images/manjusha.jpeg" alt="Manjusha Painting">
            </div>
            <p>Manjusha painting, originating from Bihar, is a unique art form known for its vibrant colors and depiction of folklore, often featuring snake motifs symbolizing legends of Bishahari.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="painting-card">
            <h2>Kerala Mural Painting</h2>
            <div class="image-container">
                <img src="/images/kerala_mural.jpeg" alt="Kerala Mural Painting">
            </div>
            <p>Kerala Mural paintings are an ancient art form that decorates temples and palaces, showcasing Hindu mythology through intricate details and natural colors.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="painting-card">
            <h2>Paithani Painting</h2>
            <div class="image-container">
                <img src="/images/paithani.jpeg" alt="Paithani Painting">
            </div>
            <p>Paithani painting, inspired by the famous Paithani sarees of Maharashtra, is known for its peacock and floral motifs, often incorporating gold and vibrant hues.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="painting-card">
            <h2>Ajanta Cave Painting</h2>
            <div class="image-container">
                <img src="/images/padampani.jpeg" alt="Ajanta Cave Painting">
            </div>
            <p>Ajanta Cave paintings, located in Maharashtra, date back to the 2nd century BCE and depict scenes from the life of Buddha, showcasing intricate details and natural pigments.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="painting-card">
            <h2>Chola Bronze Sculpture</h2>
            <div class="image-container">
                <img src="/images/chola.jpeg" alt="Chola Bronze Sculpture">
            </div>
            <p>Chola bronze sculptures, originating from Tamil Nadu, are renowned for their exquisite craftsmanship and intricate detailing, often depicting Hindu deities in dynamic poses.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="painting-card">
            <h2>Gujarat Patola Painting</h2>
            <div class="image-container">
                <img src="/images/patola.jpeg" alt="Gujarat Patola Painting">
            </div>
            <p>Patola paintings from Gujarat are known for their vibrant colors and intricate patterns, often depicting traditional motifs and scenes from daily life.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="painting-card">
            <h2>Bhujodi Painting</h2>
            <div class="image-container">
                <img src="/images/bhujodi.jpeg" alt="Bhujodi Painting">
            </div>
            <p>Bhujodi painting, originating from Gujarat, is a traditional art form that uses natural dyes and intricate patterns to depict local folklore and culture.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
